itions during coar-\n                                                                                                               signals can therefore produce disproportionately large acoustic\n                                         ticulation [10], can be estimated through Detrended Fluctua-\n                                                                                                               changes, a hallmark of deterministic chaos. Non-chaotic mod-\n                                         tion Analysis [11] and Lyapunov Exponents [12]. These multi-\n                                                                                                               els smooth out these effects, eliminating jitter, turbulence, and\n                                         scale temporal dependencies encode subtle articulatory transi-\n                                                                                                               aperiodic bursts and yielding unnaturally clean speech. Accu-\n                                         tions, co-activation patterns, and speaker-specific muscle coor-\n                                                                                                               rate EMG-to-speech synthesis thus requires non-linear chaos-\n                                         dination essential for accurate phonetic decoding in EMG-to-\n                                                                                                               inspired models that can represent both structured harmonic\n                                         Speech (ETS) conversion [4, 5].\n                                                                                                               content and chaotic, irregular dynamics.\n                                              What current ETS systems miss: Prior works [4, 5, 13]\n                                                                                    